change default orientation of arrays

because many calculations needed reshaping of the arrays to be broadcasted properly, decided to go for axis=0 as the default (i.e. expecting the time dimension to be along the first axis)

modified all the objective functions that needed to take this change into account.

/!\ discovered that the bounded version of kge and kgeprime were using the first row (i.e. the first simulation dataset) instead of the first column (that used to correspond to the KGE value). With the change of axis, this would not be an error anymore, but decided to explicit state that the whole first row is being used.

adds a non-parametric version of KGE criterion

KGEnp replaces Pearson's r by Spearman's r, and replaces bias in standard deviation by bias in flow duration curve

corrects mistake in subsetting series after change of default axis

in previous commit changing the default orientation of the array, forgot to change the order of the dimensions in the array slicing to get subset of time series where no NaN in evaluation

returns the array in the same orientation as the input array

Because HydroEval forces its own orientation in the evaluator for the objective functions to always be calculated along the same axis, the array returned by multi-component objective functions (typically KGE here) was always returning the number of simulation runs along the second axis, now it is returning along the same axis it was inputted as.
